1
00:00:00,541 --> 00:00:01,958
They took me for interrogation

2
00:00:03,250 --> 00:00:06,250
And asked, Do you need anything?

3
00:00:06,583 --> 00:00:08,458
I felt then that they wanted to release me

4
00:00:08,666 --> 00:00:09,916
I said, No, nothing

5
00:00:10,416 --> 00:00:15,291
He said, The method of interrogation will completely change

6
00:00:16,208 --> 00:00:18,333
If you have something to say

7
00:00:18,500 --> 00:00:20,958
Now is the time before they use another method

8
00:00:21,125 --> 00:00:23,291
I told him I had nothing to add

9
00:00:23,458 --> 00:00:25,041
He was expecting me to talk about weapons and such

10
00:00:25,833 --> 00:00:27,166
But I assured him I had no weapons

11
00:00:27,791 --> 00:00:31,791
And that I wasn’t the person they were looking for

12
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:34,583
He was the one responsible for what you accuse me of

13
00:00:35,166 --> 00:00:36,458
And he had been imprisoned by you before

14
00:00:37,083 --> 00:00:38,583
And it was you who released him

15
00:00:38,666 --> 00:00:41,833
So you are responsible for this mistake, not me

16
00:00:42,208 --> 00:00:44,791
He said, Alright, and sent me back

17
00:00:44,958 --> 00:00:48,000
After 10 minutes, I heard the sound of torture

18
00:00:48,666 --> 00:00:51,041
It was one of my cousins, I recognized his voice well

19
00:00:51,833 --> 00:00:55,250
They kept torturing him for two hours

20
00:00:56,958 --> 00:00:58,041
Then they summoned me for interrogation

21
00:00:58,125 --> 00:01:00,500
I realized that my turn for torture had come

22
00:01:00,791 --> 00:01:02,791
He repeated his question, Anything
new? I repeated my answer, Nothing

23
00:01:03,041 --> 00:01:06,375
They started torturing me immediately, for half an hour or an hour

24
00:01:07,041 --> 00:01:09,791
They kept torturing me until I lost consciousness

25
00:01:11,291 --> 00:01:13,666
Then they splashed me with water to wake me up

26
00:01:13,833 --> 00:01:15,791
I could hear them, but I couldn’t walk

27
00:01:16,333 --> 00:01:17,750
So they sent me back to the solitary cell

28
00:01:17,875 --> 00:01:21,583
I heard them call for Abdullah Salamah

29
00:01:22,041 --> 00:01:24,083
Both my brother and my cousin shared

30
00:01:24,208 --> 00:01:25,208
The same name

31
00:01:26,291 --> 00:01:28,500
He asked him, Are you Abu Islam? He answered, No

32
00:01:28,708 --> 00:01:30,708
So I knew they wanted my cousin

33
00:01:31,416 --> 00:01:34,875
They took him and repeated the torture on him

34
00:01:35,083 --> 00:01:36,541
He couldn’t bear it because he had asthma

35
00:01:36,666 --> 00:01:39,125
He fainted after half an hour or less

36
00:01:39,916 --> 00:01:42,833
They splashed him with water. I
heard his voice and felt reassured

37
00:01:43,958 --> 00:01:45,125
Because I had been so worried about him

38
00:01:46,375 --> 00:01:47,666
Then they took my brother for interrogation

39
00:01:49,333 --> 00:01:51,916
I started waiting to hear the sounds of torture

40
00:01:52,083 --> 00:01:53,541
Thinking they would do to him what they had done to us

41
00:01:53,625 --> 00:01:54,458
But they didn’t torture him

42
00:01:54,583 --> 00:01:56,458
Even though he stayed there for three or four hours

43
00:01:57,500 --> 00:01:59,500
They sent him back without torturing him

44
00:01:59,916 --> 00:02:01,916
Torture became a daily routine for us

45
00:02:02,625 --> 00:02:04,083
We got used to it

46
00:02:04,500 --> 00:02:05,875
Whenever we heard someone being tortured

47
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,458
We knew our turn was coming

48
00:02:09,958 --> 00:02:11,625
Once, I was asleep one afternoon

49
00:02:12,666 --> 00:02:14,875
I woke up to the sound of one of my cousins being tortured

50
00:02:15,083 --> 00:02:17,791
I knew things had become serious

51
00:02:19,250 --> 00:02:20,833
He was tortured for three hours

52
00:02:21,416 --> 00:02:24,041
Until he lost consciousness and they brought him back

53
00:02:24,250 --> 00:02:26,750
I heard the interrogator say to him

54
00:02:26,958 --> 00:02:29,083
Bring me Faraj Salamah

55
00:02:30,750 --> 00:02:34,125
He interrogated me for a short while

56
00:02:34,375 --> 00:02:37,125
I was waiting for the torture to start

57
00:02:37,375 --> 00:02:38,708
Expecting any blow

58
00:02:38,875 --> 00:02:40,375
Because I was blindfolded and handcuffed

59
00:02:41,625 --> 00:02:43,958
Then the interrogator ordered that I be
tortured by <i>shabeh</i> [suspension from the limbs]

60
00:02:44,875 --> 00:02:46,250
So I remained suspended

61
00:02:47,166 --> 00:02:51,500
I realized that my cousin hadn’t been tortured again

62
00:02:51,791 --> 00:02:56,541
Because of his illness and the interrogator’s fear of the consequences

63
00:02:56,833 --> 00:02:58,708
Since my cousin’s condition was severe

64
00:02:59,458 --> 00:03:01,083
He postponed his torture session

65
00:03:02,333 --> 00:03:04,666
As for me, I remained suspended for nine hours

66
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:07,041
Then they sent me back

67
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:10,375
I was reassured about my cousin after midnight

68
00:03:10,791 --> 00:03:12,375
When I called out to him

69
00:03:12,541 --> 00:03:15,375
He answered that he was fine, praise God

70
00:03:16,750 --> 00:03:19,166
Since then, they slightly changed their approach

71
00:03:20,791 --> 00:03:21,833
They would take us for interrogation from time to time

72
00:03:21,958 --> 00:03:25,541
But they stopped torturing us, or postponed it
